## 8. Working Conclusion

Current FE appears to be structured as:

```
App Bootstrap
    ↓
Auth Runtime
    ↓
Branch Runtime
    ↓
Transport Runtime
    ↓
Backend
```

UI surfaces such as Header, Sidebar, Layout, and Routes mostly consume runtime state rather than owning it.

The largest unresolved FE question is not Header or Sidebar. It is whether there is a dedicated route guard/auth gate. If there is no guard, the current FE relies mainly on `authStore` and `apiClient` for session recovery. That can work, but POS pages may render before auth state becomes fully known.

The next safe step is dependency mapping before any patch.
